description._content: Catalog #: 09_01871 Title: Brigadier General Clarence S. ""Bill"" Irvine Special Collection Photo Additional Information: Image shows a photograph of Clarence S. Irvine. Caption reads ""C. S. ""Bill"" Irvine United States Army at Paterson, NJ. November 4, 1936, Brigadier General Clarence Irvine enjoyed a long distinguished military career, mainly involving engineering. He served with the XXI Bomber Command (B-29's) during WWII and continued to serve throughout the 1950s and 1960s. Tags: Brigadier General Clarence S.
